The paper deals with the development of a self-adaptive neurofuzzy system for handling data streams in real-time. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of hyperplane clustering, which is a technique used in data mining and pattern recognition, and hence could be classified under cs.DM (Data Mining) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of network parameters, which is a common problem in neural networks, and hence could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the application of the proposed model in the field of autonomous vehicles, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
